response:
Let's denote $z = \tan\frac{\pi}{5}$.  Then our quantity becomes $\frac{z + i}{z - i}$.  We can i...</ thought process ...
\begin{align*}
   \frac{z + i}{z - i} &= \frac1{z - i} + \frac1{z - i}i^2 \\
                    &= -\frac{z + i}{z^2 + 1} \\
                    &= -\frac{z^2 - 1 + (z - i)}{z^2 + 1} \\
                    &= \frac{1}{1 - z^2} - i\frac{z}{z^2 + 1}
\end{align*}
So it corresponds to $n = \frac{1}{1 - z^2} \pmod{10}$ and $z \equiv \frac{10^n - 1}{10^n + 1} \pmod{10}$.  Plugging in the values $z \equiv 0,2,4,6,8 \pmod{10}$ gives $n\equiv 0,2,7,6,9 \pmod{10}$.  Taking $n\pmod{10}$ of none of those values gives us $n=7$....
The answer: $7$.

